      "id": "0x245e440c3b517a0b7a7ff11c2c038cfd96c503ab9cbf3e593bd8d7c73cd07fae",
      "title": "ICCP-3 Defining Vault Revenue & Distributions for Future DAO Product Directions ",
      "content": "[ICCP-3 Defining Vault Revenue & Distributions for Future DAO Product Directions ](https://github.com/IlluviumGame/IIPs/pull/35/)\n## Simple Summary\nThis ICCP defines how future product revenue is distributed to the Vault, accounting for variable and fixed costs. Revenue from products with low variable costs is 100% of all ETH generated from sales. Revenue from products with non-negligible variable costs is less variable costs. Revenue from partnerships is the DAO's portion of agreements, less non-negligible variable costs. Commissions and affiliate marketing are considered. Variable and fixed costs incurred outside the DAO's core competency are deducted from revenue for experiential events before being sent to the Vault. Future product proposals should use the relevant definition of distribution.\n## Abstract\nThe Illuvium DAO has expanded and clarified its vision since its inception, so it's vital to define revenue from different products before launching new product streams. This aims to create clear definitions for future product lines and how revenue will be distributed to the Vault.\n## Overview\nThe Illuvium DAO will release various products in 2023, including the main game, mobile game, collection game, merchandise, and festivals. To ensure consistency in revenue distribution via the Vault, the DAO must clarify definitions for revenue from these differing products.\nProposals for new products/revenue streams should identify the relevant distribution definition. Negligible variable cost (information) products will send 100% of revenue to the Vault, while non-negligible variable cost (physical) products will send 100% of revenue less variable costs to the Vault. Commission and affiliate marketing products will also follow the relevant distribution strategy, with revenue reduced by associated costs.\nThe DAO may also engage in partnerships and licensing of assets. Partnership products will send 100% of revenue attributable to Illuvium's portion of the agreement, less variable costs, to the Vault. Licensing products will send 100% of revenue to the DAO per the licensing agreement to the Vault.\nEvent/experiential products have unique costs outside the DAO's core competency. Revenue distributions from such products will be less non-negligible variable costs and event/experience-specific fixed costs to the Vault.\n## Rationale\nThe purpose of this proposal is to clearly define the revenue and expectations for Vault distributions for the Illuvium DAO as it expands its scope and product offerings. The proposal aims to ensure sustainable revenue distribution for the long-term operation of the DAO, maintain quality in all products, and provide clear expectations for $ILV stakers.\n",
